cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.MA 

The paper introduces a new framework for mechanism design that extends the standard game theoretic framework to allow for uncertainty about execution. This falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of task allocation is also a distributed computing problem (cs.DC). The technical results presented in the paper involve incentive compatibility, individual rationality, and efficiency, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
